reviews.review_text: Could be a bit more warped Checked out the La Bamba.  It's definitely here.  Never heard a worse recording in my life.  If you're into strange ambience and twistedness, this one's for you.  0 stars.
Nicely Done If this is indeed oneof teh NYC shows with Jorma then well done and thank you very much.

People Aren't Going to Believe this Tape Thanx SirMick.  During Come Back Baby, presumably the taper, states the title of this review.  38 years later I can say I appreciate your efforts.  I have the worst sounding Dead tape ever in my collection, as a reference.  While the sound at times, John's Other, is bloomin' awful, some of it isn't too bad.  As a dead head you need to at least hear it.  I am opening my radio show this week with Ode to Billie Dean, which sounds pretty good actually!  Peace

It's a Smoker Just needs a little eq and it sounds fine; about what you'd expect considering the lineage.  Personally I'm grateful to have this unique show. 
 Thank You!  Five stars to offset the other bozos.

Has it's moments Very nice transition from Cryptical -> Sugar Mags

Hard to give it more than 2 stars.

For TRUE Heads only Sure you give this show a poor rating if you're not DEAD to the core!  But I give it the highest rating: incredible set list and very well played.  Bozos: no-no. Dead to the core: Yabadabadoo!

good to hear this good to hear, but difficult listening. 
as i always say, we Deadheads learn to listen past the noise. 
upgraded one star for the unique situation.
